title.rendered: Afghanistan vs Pakistan, 1st T20I 2023: Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
Fantasy Team for Afghanistan vs Pakistan, 1st T20I

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on the basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Afghanistan & Pakistan Playing XIs

Afghanistan: Rahmanullah Gurbaz (wk), Usman Ghani, Ibrahim Zadran, Najibullah Zadran, Karim Janat/ Fareed Ahmad, Mohammad Nabi, Gulbadin Naib, Rashid Khan (c), Naveen-ul-Haq, Mujeeb Ur Rahman, Fazalhaq Farooqi

Pakistan: Shan Masood, Mohammad Haris, Saim Ayub/Tayyab Tahir, Azam Khan (wk), Iftikhar Ahmed, Shadab Khan (c), Imad Wasim, Faheem Ashraf, Naseem Shah, Zaman Khan, Ihsanullah

Pitch Report for Sharjah Cricket Stadium

Venue: Sharjah Cricket Stadium, Sharjah

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 166

2nd innings average score: 120

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Slow

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Imad Wasim has been a hot property in fantasy leagues lately. In his last 10 T20s, he hammered 364 runs at a colossal average of 121 including the highest score of 92* and took 13 wickets.

Through calculated stroke play, Ibrahim Zadran accumulated 330 runs at 47 in his last 10 T20Is – of which 117 runs at 59 came in Sharjah.

Rashid Khan has gone wicketless only once in his last 10 outings, bagging 19 wickets including the best figures of four for 21.

Fazalhaq Farooqi is coming from a highly successful time (11 wickets), including three three-fors in the Pakistan T20 League. Moreover, he also ended up with a three-wicket haul in his only T20I game against Pakistan.

Mohammad Haris’ recent form augurs well for fantasy players. His latest scores read 85, 34, 79, and 35. He finished the Pakistan T20 league with a strike rate of 186.

In the same tournament, Zaman Khan and Ihsanullah bagged a whopping 37 wickets between them at a combined strike rate of 14.5.

In six games at the Sharjah Cricket Stadium, Mujeeb Ur Rahman has taken 12 wickets – of which nine have come bowling second.

The only time Shadab Khan batted in a T20I in Sharjah, he scored 36. In addition, he has picked seven wickets, including the best figures of four for eight at the venue.

Mohammad Nabi has managed only 45 runs and seven wickets in his last 10 competitive T20s.
